{
  "global": "Apply magnetostatic superposition—full disk equals annular disk plus removed small disk—to write B₁ = B₀ − B_small, then use the closed-form axial-field formula for a uniformly magnetized disk to express B_small in terms of B₀, R, and d.",
  "subtasks": [
    {
      "subtask": "Establish the superposition decomposition of the three configurations",
      "atomics": [
        "Identify that the full disk (radius 2R, magnetization M) equals the annular disk (inner radius R, outer radius 2R) plus the removed small disk (radius R), all with the same uniform magnetization M",
        "Apply linearity of B to write B₀ = B₁ + B_small at the common evaluation point (geometric center), giving B₁ = B₀ − B_small"
      ]
    },
    {
      "subtask": "Derive the axial field at the center of a uniformly magnetized disk of radius a using the magnetic surface charge model",
      "atomics": [
        "Replace uniform magnetization M (in ẑ direction) with equivalent surface magnetic charges: σ_m = +M on the top face (z = +d/2) and σ_m = −M on the bottom face (z = −d/2), each of radius a",
        "Apply the axial H-field formula for a uniformly charged disk: H_z = (σ_m/2)[1 − z/√(z² + a²)] with z = d/2 for each face, noting sign reversal for the point below a face",
        "Sum both face contributions to obtain H_z^total = −M[1 − (d/2)/√((d/2)² + a²)]",
        "Convert to B via B = μ₀(H + M): B_z = μ₀M·(d/2)/√((d/2)² + a²), which simplifies to B_disk = μ₀Md/√(d² + 4a²)"
      ]
    },
    {
      "subtask": "Evaluate B₀ and B_small using the derived formula with the respective radii",
      "atomics": [
        "Substitute a = 2R: B₀ = μ₀Md/√(d² + 16R²)",
        "Substitute a = R: B_small = μ₀Md/√(d² + 4R²)"
      ]
    },
    {
      "subtask": "Express B_small as a ratio times B₀ to eliminate the unknown μ₀M",
      "atomics": [
        "Form the ratio B_small/B₀ = √(d² + 16R²)/√(d² + 4R²) by dividing the two expressions",
        "Write B⃗_small = B⃗₀ · √(d² + 16R²)/√(d² + 4R²)"
      ]
    },
    {
      "subtask": "Compute B⃗₁ and verify sign and limiting behavior",
      "atomics": [
        "Substitute into B⃗₁ = B⃗₀ − B⃗_small to obtain B⃗₁ = B⃗₀ · [√(d² + 4R²) − √(d² + 16R²)] / √(d² + 4R²)",
        "Confirm sign: since √(d² + 16R²) > √(d² + 4R²), the bracket is negative, so B⃗₁ is antiparallel to B⃗₀",
        "Check d ≪ R limit: B₀ ≈ μ₀Md/(4R), B_small ≈ μ₀Md/(2R) = 2B₀, so B₁ ≈ −B₀, consistent with the ratio approaching 2"
      ]
    }
  ],
  "global_atomics": [
    "Confirm the single common evaluation point: the center of the full disk, the center of the removed disk, and the center of the hollowed region are all the same point (0, 0, 0), validating the superposition application"
  ],
  "gold_actions": {
    "global": "Use B⃗₁ = B⃗₀ − B⃗_small with B_disk = μ₀Md/√(d² + 4a²) to obtain B⃗₁ = B⃗₀ · [√(d² + 4R²) − √(d² + 16R²)] / √(d² + 4R²)",
    "subtasks": [
      {
        "subtask": "Write B⃗₁ = B⃗₀ − B⃗_small from linearity of magnetostatics applied to the three-disk decomposition",
        "atomics": [
          "State decomposition: (full disk, r = 2R) = (annular disk, R < r < 2R) + (small disk, r = R), all with magnetization M",
          "Apply B-field linearity: B⃗₀ = B⃗₁ + B⃗_small ⟹ B⃗₁ = B⃗₀ − B⃗_small, all evaluated at the center (0,0,0)"
        ]
      },
      {
        "subtask": "Derive B_disk = μ₀Md/√(d² + 4a²) for a disk of radius a via magnetic surface charges",
        "atomics": [
          "Assign σ_m = +M at z = +d/2 and σ_m = −M at z = −d/2 (radius a each) to replace uniform M",
          "Apply H_z = (σ_m/2)[1 − z/√(z² + a²)] with z = d/2 for each face (with sign for point below top face)",
          "Sum: H_z^total = −M · [1 − (d/2)/√((d/2)² + a²)]",
          "Apply B_z = μ₀(H_z + M) = μ₀M · (d/2)/√((d/2)² + a²) = μ₀Md / √(d² + 4a²)"
        ]
      },
      {
        "subtask": "Compute B₀ = μ₀Md/√(d² + 16R²) and B_small = μ₀Md/√(d² + 4R²) by plugging in radii",
        "atomics": [
          "Plug a = 2R: B₀ = μ₀Md / √(d² + 4·(2R)²) = μ₀Md / √(d² + 16R²)",
          "Plug a = R: B_small = μ₀Md / √(d² + 4R²)"
        ]
      },
      {
        "subtask": "Form ratio B_small/B₀ = √(d² + 16R²)/√(d² + 4R²) to eliminate μ₀M",
        "atomics": [
          "Divide: B_small/B₀ = [μ₀Md/√(d² + 4R²)] / [μ₀Md/√(d² + 16R²)] = √(d² + 16R²)/√(d² + 4R²)",
          "Write B⃗_small = B⃗₀ · √(d² + 16R²)/√(d² + 4R²)"
        ]
      },
      {
        "subtask": "Subtract to get B⃗₁ = B⃗₀[√(d² + 4R²) − √(d² + 16R²)]/√(d² + 4R²) and verify sign and limits",
        "atomics": [
          "Compute B⃗₁ = B⃗₀[1 − √(d² + 16R²)/√(d² + 4R²)] = B⃗₀[√(d² + 4R²) − √(d² + 16R²)]/√(d² + 4R²)",
          "Note bracket is negative ⟹ B⃗₁ antiparallel to B⃗₀ (field at center of hole reversed relative to original field)",
          "Verify d ≪ R: B₀ ≈ μ₀Md/(4R), B_small ≈ μ₀Md/(2R) = 2B₀, so B₁ ≈ −B₀ ✓"
        ]
      }
    ],
    "global_atomics": [
      "Verify all three fields (B⃗₀ for full disk, B⃗_small for removed disk, B⃗₁ for annular disk) are evaluated at the identical point (0,0,0), confirming superposition validity"
    ]
  }
}
```

FINAL ANSWER: $\vec{B}_1 = \vec{B}_0 \dfrac{\sqrt{d^2 + 4R^2} - \sqrt{d^2 + 16R^2}}{\sqrt{d^2 + 4R^2}}$
